            "solution_text": "\\(5^{2x+1} = 25^{y-3}\\)\n\\(5^{2x+1} = (5^2)^{y-3}\\)\n\\(5^{2x+1} = 5^{2(y-3)}\\)\nSince the bases are equal, the exponents must also be equal:\n\\(2x + 1 = 2(y - 3)\\)\n\\(2x + 1 = 2y - 6\\)"
